<paragraph blockId="9.[446,802,1501,1557]" box="[507,740,1533,1557]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">
(
<figureCitation box="[515,661,1533,1557]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[212,279,1585,1607]" captionTargetBox="[238,1143,178,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-46@4.[238,1144,177,1556]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Frons and palpus of male. (A, B) Pseudostegana acutifoliolata sp. nov.; (C,D) Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov.; (E,F) Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov.; (G,H) Pseudostegana minutipalpata sp. nov.; (I,J) Pseudostegana insularis sp. nov.; (K,L) Pseudostegana silvana sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209711/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">Figure 1C,D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[673,707,1533,1557]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[212,279,1137,1159]" captionTargetBox="[240,1144,176,1106]" captionTargetId="figure-263@6.[240,1145,175,1107]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Wing of male: (A). Pseudostegana acutifoliolata sp. nov.; (B) Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov.; (C) Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov.; (D Pseudostegana minutipalpata sp. nov.; (E) Pseudostegana insularis sp. nov.; (F) Pseudostegana silvana sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209715/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">2B</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[718,732,1533,1557]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">4</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,253,1605,1629]" box="[144,253,1605,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">
<emphasis box="[144,253,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[144,1103,1645,1701]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">
Medial, dark band much broadened and with one distinct, protruded part submedially (
<figureCitation box="[199,316,1677,1701]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[212,279,1137,1159]" captionTargetBox="[240,1144,176,1106]" captionTargetId="figure-263@6.[240,1145,175,1107]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Wing of male: (A). Pseudostegana acutifoliolata sp. nov.; (B) Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov.; (C) Pseudostegana bipartita sp. nov.; (D Pseudostegana minutipalpata sp. nov.; (E) Pseudostegana insularis sp. nov.; (F) Pseudostegana silvana sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209715/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
); paramere shallow split apically in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[865,983,1677,1701]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1408">Figure 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409" startId="10.[212,279,901,923]" targetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1173,901,982]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
Figure 4. 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Gao &amp; Chen, 2010" authorityName="Li &amp; Gao &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2010" box="[316,550,902,924]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Pseudostegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[316,550,902,924]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Pseudostegana bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[557,640,902,923]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,340,1049,1073]" box="[212,340,1049,1073]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,340,1049,1073]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,683,1089,1113]" box="[212,683,1089,1113]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Only important characters are given here.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1169,1289]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,280,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Head.</emphasis>
Ocellar triangle mostly brownish black, brown on lower a quarter. Frons brown. Pedicel greyish brown above, greyish yellow below; first flagellomere greyish yellow on inner one-third, dark brown on outer two-thirds. Face brownish black. Clypeus dark brown. Gena brown. Palpus brown and slender, rod-shaped in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1345,1401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,293,1345,1369]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Thorax</emphasis>
. Scutum yellow on anterior half, brown on posterior half. Pleura brown to black. Katepisternal setae two. Scutellum brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,847,1457,1481]" box="[212,847,1457,1481]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,272,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Legs.</emphasis>
Yellow, black on knee joints of mid- and hindlegs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1537,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,317,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites glossy, yellow on first and second, dark brown on the rest. Sternites greyish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[212,1172,1628,1684]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">
<emphasis box="[212,402,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium roundly protruded on ventral margin, with about 23 setae (
<figureCitation box="[289,417,1660,1684]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Figure 4A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus protruded on posteroventral corner (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1159,1660,1684]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1409">Figure 4A,B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1104,167,223]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">
Cercus ventrally round (
<figureCitation box="[444,598,167,191]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Figure 4A,B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically sclerotized, round in ventral view, pointed in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[561,708,199,223]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[212,279,901,923]" captionTargetBox="[216,1167,173,872]" captionTargetId="figure-170@10.[213,1170,172,872]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Pseudostegana bilobata sp. nov., male. (A) epandrium, cercus and surstylus; (B) surstylus; (C) cercus; (D,E) hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. For orientations and organizations see Figure 3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5209719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5209719/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1410">Figure 4D,E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
